                            <comment id="14709717" author="stack" created="Mon, 24 Aug 2015 17:50:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What version of hbase is this patch made against? Have you seen the scan redo in hbase 1.1?  See &lt;a href=&quot;https://blogs.apache.org/hbase/entry/scan_improvements_in_hbase_1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://blogs.apache.org/hbase/entry/scan_improvements_in_hbase_1&lt;/a&gt;  Does this get you what you need?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14710620" author="cong.han" created="Tue, 25 Aug 2015 05:39:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch is made against version 2.0.0,And the aim of this patch is to limit the return size of row(Result Object) from server,Not  the heapSize of the return cell,It&apos;s an replacement of PageFilter,cause the PageFilter cannot guarantee that the number of results returned  to a client are &amp;lt;= page size,Everytime I use PageFilter,I write code like this&lt;br/&gt;
int count = 0;&lt;br/&gt;
for(Result result:resultScanner){&lt;br/&gt;
     //operation&lt;br/&gt;
     count++;&lt;br/&gt;
     if(count&amp;gt;limit)&lt;/p&gt;
{
           break;
     }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s not good for user experience&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
